HEADWORD: Lunaria
<hw>Lunaria</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A small genus of European
herbs of the mustard family, including the herb <stype>honesty</stype>
(<spn>Lunaria annua</spn>), which is also called <stype>moonwort</stype>
and <stype>lunary</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Lunaria</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

